    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae4b46ac_4fa2061b",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrSurfaceDrawContext.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 747,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-18T15:36:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we quite need all of this, and rectStaysRect() can be tricky for this sort of thing since 90degree and axis flips will change how the local coordinates should line up, whereas mapRect sorts the ltrb (if I remember correctly for my own bugs in the past).  The GrQuad::asRect() checks for this in its return value, so it\u0027s safer than viewMatrix.rectStaysRect().\n\nGiven that, and that attemptQuadOptimization modifies the input DrawQuad in these same circumstances as (clip \u0026\u0026 viewMatrix.rectStaysRect()), I think we can just reconstruct the croppedRect and croppedLocal from the modified DrawQuad instead of defining a new crop_rect function. It would be something like:\n\n   if (clip \u0026\u0026 opt \u003d\u003d QuadOptimization::kClipApplied \u0026\u0026 quad.fDeviceQuad.asRect(\u0026croppedRect)) {\n       SkASSERT(viewMatrix.rectStaysRect());\n       SkAssertResult(quad.fLocalQuad.asRect(\u0026croppedLocal));\n       // Make croppedRect local to viewMatrix, which we know is safe and preserves the relationship with local since asRect returned true.\n       viewMatrix.inverseMapRect(\u0026croppedRect);\n       clip \u003d nullptr; // Explicitly null so it\u0027s completely skipped by addDrawOp\n   } else {\n       // Even if attemptQuadOptimization modified \u0027quad\u0027, we can\u0027t reconstruct what we need for FillRRectOp, so use the original coords and clip\n       croppedRect \u003d rectToDraw;\n       croppedLocal \u003d localRect;\n   }",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 738,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 747,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "24bf9efc41528e80bf3ab8cc692aaaa1b92bde9b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
